    "Pioneering works on the diffusion of misinformation through social media have helped to improve our understanding of the mechanisms that likely underlie this phenomenon (see, e.g., [4,25,31,37,65,82]), but the field is still confronted with significant questions and (methodological) challenges: For instance, there is still no broadly accepted conceptual framework of terms related to the issue (see, e.g., [30,85]), nor are there sophisticated answers to the relevant question of how common misinformation actually is [37] and what its short-and long-term effects are [83].One reason for these gaps in knowledge is that there is thus far no broadly accepted pool of methods to collect and analyze online misinformation data.",
